<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id129094bb-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c" identifier="/us/usc/t4/s146"><num value="146">§ 146.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purposes of this chapter, there are authorized to be appropriated, out of any money in the Treasury not otherwise appropriated, sums of not more than $50,000 for any one fiscal year.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id129094bc-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c">(Added <ref href="/us/act/1951-10-31/ch655/s12">Oct. 31, 1951, ch. 655, § 12</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/65/715">65 Stat. 715</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
